{{one source|date=February 2016}} [[Image:Jake The Alligator Man.jpg|right|thumb|250px|Jake in his display case at Marsh's Free Museum in [[Long Beach, Washington]]]] [[File:Marsh's Free Museum - Long Beach, Washington.jpg|thumb|250px|Marsh's Free Museum, where Jake is located]] '''Jake the Alligator Man''' is an alleged half-man, half-[[alligator]] creature on display in apparently [[Mummy|mummified]] condition at Marsh's Free Museum, a [[tourist trap]] located at 409 South Pacific Avenue in [[Long Beach, Washington]]. He was acquired by the Marshes for $750 in 1967 from an [[Antique shop|antique store]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.columbian.com/news/strange/outerlimits/alligator.cfm |title='Alligator Man' of Long Beach: His past is a murky swamp of tall tales |author=Staff writer |website=The Columbian |location=Clark County, Washington |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070906051510/http://www.columbian.com/news/strange/outerlimits/alligator.cfm |archive-date=September 6, 2007 |dead-url=yes}}</ref>
A postcard image was used by the ''[[Weekly World News]]'' on November 9, 1993 for front-page article, "Half-human, half-alligator discovered in Florida swamp."<ref>{{cite news|last=McGuire|first=Mickey|title=Half-human, half-alligator discovered in Florida swamp|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-u0DAAAAMBAJ&printsec=frontcover&lr=#v=onepage&q&f=false|accessdate=2 April 2013|newspaper=Weekly World News|date=November 9, 1993|location=Naples, Fla.|pages=8–9|volume=15|issue=6}}</ref> The periodical subsequently reported on his escape from captivity, killing of a [[Miami, Florida|Miami]] man, and giving birth.
Jake has acquired a [[cult following]] in [[Pacific Northwest|Northwestern]] [[popular culture]]. His 75th birthday party is held annually<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.discoverourcoast.com/activities/jake-the-alligator-man-celebrates-75th-birthday-again/|title=Jake the Alligator Man celebrates 75th birthday ... again - Our CoastOur Coast|website=www.discoverourcoast.com|access-date=2016-08-25}}</ref> in early August on the [[Long Beach Peninsula|peninsula]], and features events such as a [[bachelor party]], [[Auto show|car show]], bridal contest, and live music.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jakethealligatorman.com/|title=Join Us - Jake the Alligator Man|website=Jake the Alligator Man|language=en-US|access-date=2016-08-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://funbeach.com/event/jake-the-alligator-mans-birthday-long-beach/|title=Jake the Alligator Man's Birthday & Car Show|language=en-US|access-date=2016-08-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nwescapes.cityvoter.com/annual-jake-the-alligator-man-75th-birthday-party-and-car-show/biz/697247|title=Annual Jake the Alligator Man 75th Birthday Party & Car Show - KING5 Best Northwest Escapes|website=nwescapes.cityvoter.com|access-date=2016-08-25}}</ref> [[Bumper stickers]] featuring the oddity can be commonly seen throughout [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]] and [[Oregon]].{{citation needed|date=December 2013}}
